TextChange: Soda pop is a good example. It is a very unhealthful product which leads to childhood and adulthood obesity for a significant proportion of the population. But the advertisements only tell us how great the beverages taste, never how unhealthy they are. People would be better off drinking tap water, but the smiling faces of people enjoying soda convince people to buy the stuff.
